{{hatnote|Alexander von Humboldt Medal redirects here. For another award of the same name, see [[European Geosciences Union]]}} {{Infobox organization |name =International Association for Vegetation Science |image = |image_border = |abbreviation = IAVS |motto = |formation = |type = |purpose = |headquarters = |website = [http://www.iavs.org/About.aspx www.iavs.org] }}
The '''International Association for Vegetation Science''' (IAVS) promotes contact between scientists and others interested in the study of vegetation [[ecology]], promotes research and publication of research results. In 1939 the '''International Phytosociological Society''' (IPS) was founded, with its headquarters in [[Montpellier]], France. After the [[Second World War]] it was reconstituted as the '''Internationale Vereinigung für Vegetationskunde (IVV)''', which adopted a constitution at the [[International Botanical Congress]] of 1954. The current name was adopted in 1981–82.<ref>[http://www.iavs.org/Abouthistory.aspx IAVS history] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090727101843/http://www.iavs.org/AboutHistory.aspx |date=2009-07-27 }}</ref>
==Publications== The society publishes:<ref>[http://www.iavs.org/Publication.aspx IAVS publications] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151221073531/http://iavs.org/Publication.aspx |date=2015-12-21 }}</ref> * ''[[IAVS Bulletin]]'' * ''[[Journal of Vegetation Science]]'' * ''[[Applied Vegetation Science]]'' * ''[[Resolutions (journal)|Resolutions]]''
==Awards== The '''Alexander von Humboldt Medal''' is a prize awarded biennially from 2011 onwards by the association. The award is intended to honor scientists who have contributed greatly to the intellectual development and advancement of vegetation science and plant community ecology. '''Honorary membership''' is also bestowed by the society.
===Medal recipients=== *'''2011''' [[J. Philip Grime]]<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.iavs.org/uploads/PG-Pres.pdf |year=2011 |title=2011 Alexander von Humboldt Medal J. Philip Grime |author=Jason Fridley}}</ref> *'''2013''' [[David Tilman]]<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.iavs.org/uploads/PG-Pres.pdf |year=2013 |title=2013 Alexander von Humboldt Medal David Tilman |author=Jason Fridley}}</ref> *'''2015''' [[Sandra Lavorel]]<ref>{{citation|url=https://www.iavs.org/AwardsHonorary.aspx |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090727101910/http://www.iavs.org/AwardsHonorary.aspx |dead-url=yes |archive-date=27 July 2009 |title=Honorary Membership -and- The Alexander von Humboldt Medal |accessdate=16 December 2015 |df= }} </ref> *'''2017''' [[F. Stuart Chapin III]]<ref>http://iavs.org/Awards/Alexander-von-Humboldt/Chapin-Intro.aspx</ref>
