'''Myrsini Malakou''' is a Greek biologist. She was awarded the [[Goldman Environmental Prize]] in 2001, for her contributions to the protection of the wetlands of [[Lake Prespa|Préspa]], jointly with fellow biologist [[Giorgos Catsadorakis]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goldmanprize.org/node/90|title=Europe 2001. Giorgos Catsadorakis & Myrsini Malakou. Greece. Land Preservation|publisher=[[Goldman Environmental Prize]]|accessdate=21 November 2010|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101123042728/http://goldmanprize.org/node/90|archivedate=23 November 2010|df=}}</ref>

